  • Package pcd.data

    • Class pcd.data.ImageDataObject extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • pointList

          ArrayList<E> pointList
          A list of PcdPoint
          See Also:
          PcdPoint

        • imgPath

          String imgPath
          An absolute String path to associated image file

        • layer

          PointOverlay layer
          A Graphics2D based overlay to draw points over the image.
          See Also:
          It also uses the OverlayComponent which is JComponent implementing an overlay.

        • initialized

          boolean initialized
          Determines whether the image object has been initialized with points
          See Also:
          ImageDataObject.pointList, ImageDataObject.initialize(java.util.ArrayList<pcd.data.PcdPoint>, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer>, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String>, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String>)

        • angleInitialized

          boolean angleInitialized
          Determined whether the ImageDataObject.pointList has been initialized with angles
          See Also:
          ImageDataObject.angleInitialize(double, int)

        • avgAngle

          double avgAngle
          The normalized average of all points of the image object. The normalized angle is the average of all angles shifted to a 0-180 degree range.

        • stdAngle

          double stdAngle
          Standard deviations of all ImageDataObject.pointList point angles from average. Angles of points must be normalized before calculating deviation
          See Also:
          ImageDataObject.avgAngle

    • Class pcd.data.PcdPoint extends Point implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • cilia_type

          int cilia_type
          The type of the cilia, matching ID from config.

        • selected

          boolean selected
          Whether or not the point should appear larger when drawn, due to selection.

        • score

          double score
          The confidence score, as returned by the Python process. It is by default 1.0 in the case it is added by a doctor.

        • angle

          double angle
          The angle of the central pair of microtubules in a cilium, important for establishing a diagnosis based on quantitative analysis by the software. The angle is always only in the range 0 to 90.

        • anglePositive

          boolean anglePositive
          Whether the angle is in the 4th of 1st quadrant. 1st if true.

        • typeName

          String typeName
          The name of the cilium type associated with its ID based on config.
